<DocsLayout title="buoy context" description="Generate design system context for CLAUDE.md">
  <h1>buoy context</h1>

  <p>
    Generate design system context to add to your CLAUDE.md file. Gives AI
    assistants the information they need to write design-compliant code.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <pre><code>buoy context [options]</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Option</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>-o, --output &lt;path&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Output file path (default: stdout)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--append</code></td>
        <td>Append to CLAUDE.md in current directory</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>-d, --detail &lt;level&gt;</code></td>
        <td>Detail level: minimal, standard, comprehensive (default: "standard")</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--no-tokens</code></td>
        <td>Exclude token information</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--no-components</code></td>
        <td>Exclude component information</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--no-validation</code></td>
        <td>Exclude validation commands</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--json</code></td>
        <td>Output as JSON with stats</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Examples</h2>

  <h3>Generate and append to CLAUDE.md</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy context --append

Added design system section to CLAUDE.md</code></pre>

  <h3>Preview context</h3>

  <pre><code>$ buoy context

## Design System

### Available Components
- Button (variant, size, disabled)
- Card (padding, shadow)
- Modal (open, onClose)

### Design Tokens
Use these instead of hardcoded values:
- Colors: primary, secondary, success, error
- Spacing: sm (8px), md (16px), lg (24px)

### Validation
Run `buoy check` before committing.</code></pre>

  <h2>Detail Levels</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>minimal</strong> - Component list and basic rules (~200 tokens)</li>
    <li><strong>standard</strong> - Components, tokens, and validation (~500 tokens)</li>
    <li><strong>comprehensive</strong> - Full documentation (~1500 tokens)</li>
  </ul>

